\lex corkosor
\ps n
\mtyp stem
\de negotiation.about.a.wedding
\seme literally 'the thief's voice'
\seme In traditional Kiranti marriage culture, if a girl does not agree to marry the boy who chose her, he can also convince her forcefully. This process is known as "stealing the girl" (nep. 'cornu'). Some relatives of the boy visit the girls home, inform her family and try to negotiate for the marriage. This is called 'corkosor', because they raise the voice of the thief to convince the girl's family.
\gn चोरको सोर
\lg N
\ex Ketaŋa keti lemdutadomo panta corkosor khaiʔma.
\exe If a boy woes a girl, one has to start the negotiations.
\exn आ..., केटाले फकाइल्यायो भने चोरको सोर जानुपर्छ।
\exsrc LH_Lal.0595
\qst

