\lex -ko
\alt -kko
\ps gm
\mtyp affix
\de LOC.NMLZ 
\seme nominalised locative (< -iʔ-ko), genitive
\gn -को
\lg C
\com Various evidence suggests that the genitive is derived from -iʔ-ko [-LOC-NMLZ] (< older *-t-ko). This is still best visible when the genitive directly follows an accented vowel, most frequently with sa 'who'. In this case, it has alternatives -kko, -ʔko, -iko, -iʔko. The present gloss is meant as a remedy against earlier difficulties with separating -iʔ-ko [-LOC-NMLZ] and -ko [GEN]. 
\qst

