\lex khencomma
\ps n
\mtyp stem
\de soul.raising
\seme It is believed that the soul (kheĩ) can fall down from its location close to the head on various occasions, which brings ill luck so that it has to be raised again (coms-, also kopt- 'pick up'). Soul raising is part of some rituals but also is a common everyday practice because people (especially children) are believed to drop their soul (tha-, thand-) when they are shocked. 
