\lex som
\ps n
\mtyp stem
\de liver
\gn कलेजो
\lg C
\qst Out of the only two corpus instances where som appears outside som si-/som set- one instance has 'liver'/कलेजो in the translation, the other 'lung'/फोकसो.  An informant also said that som and somphorok ('lung'/फोक्सो) are more or less synonyms (+ cf. their etymological relation). On the other hand, the translation as 'liver'/कलेजो  fits better with the use in som si-/som set-, as the liver is more commonly viewed as the seat of emotions. कलेजो is also the translation in the community dictionary. It has been chosen as the final version here because there are no good competitors for कलेजो.

