\lex tukt
\ct som tukma; sawa tukma
\morph tuk
\ps vt
\mtyp stem
\val A-ERG P-NOM poss(A)-EMO V-a(A).o(P); A-ERG P-NOM poss(A)-EMO V-a(3s).o(P)
\de have.feelings.for; like; love; feel.sorry.for; take.pity.on; worry.about; be.anxious.about
\gn माया गर्नु; दया गर्नु
\lg C
\ety prob. tuk- 'ache' + t-augment [APPL], i.e. 'have one's X ache for'
\ex Huĩsaŋa hiccibaŋ warisamace usom tuktukuce.
\exe He's in love with two girls.
\exn उसले दुइटी केटीसँग माया गर्छ ।
\exsrc field notes ROS
\ex Ani taiyaktiŋago makhae? - Manchi hou! Manchi haŋ akka asom tuknanihẽ phe naŋ.
\exe Did you see us come? - No! Otherwise I would have taken pity on you (and let you in).
\exn हामी आउँदै गरेको देख्यौ ? - छैन ! नत्र तिमीहरूलाई (भित्र बोलाएर) दया गर्थें त ।
\exsrc them_talk.080 - 082
\ex Mikha cha gari lo unari aŋ lisakha aŋ, ekdam asuk anisawa tuktuyaktoke kha, abo asuk mojja nude.
\exe When she was a child her nose looked weird, we were all very worried about her, but now everything's fine.
\exn सानो हुँदा उसको नाक कस्तो देखिन्थ्यो, कस्तो माया लाग्दो, अहिले त कति राम्रो निको भयो । 
\exsrc CLDLCh2R04S04.143
\com This verb is used together with two different possessed EMO nouns. With som 'feelings' (< 'liver') it means 'love, pity'. With sawa 'strength' it means 'worry about'. 
\qst

