\morph waʔ
\morph waiʔ
\morph wac
\morph was
\ps v2
\mtyp v2
\de COMPL
\gn वर्नु
\lg C
\com This forms is best described as a V2 because it has verbal characteristics and must occur with another verb before it. However, it is different from all other V2 in that it does not require suffix copying. Instead, both V1 and watt- are fully inflected, e.g. kob-e watt-e [pick.up-IND.PST COMPL-IND.PST]instead of kob-u-watt-e or cokt-u-c-e watt-u-c-e [join-3P-3nsP-IND.PST COMPL-3P-3nsP-IND.PST] instead of cokt-u-watt-u-c-e. 
\qst precise semantics of this v2 remains to be established
\qst

